  "source_url": "https://arsheriffs.org/asa-directory/sheriff-directory/",
  "source_dataset": "county_sheriffs",
  "note": "75 of 75 counties returned, all individually web-verified against county sheriff sites, county government pages, the Arkansas Sheriffs' Association, and/or Ballotpedia. 2026 is a sheriff election year (4-year terms; winners seated 2027-01-01), so every record reflects the CURRENT officeholder as of 2026-07-03, not primary/general-election winners. Mid-term turnover captured: Hot Spring (Richard Tolleson, appointed 2025-03-11 after Finkbeiner resigned), Union (Charlie Phillips, appointed Nov 2025 after Ricky Roberts resigned), Sebastian (Mike Conger, interim from 2026-04-01 after Hobe Runion retired). Incumbents not returning in 2027 but still serving through 2026-12-31: Baxter (Montgomery), Boone (Roy Martin), Cleveland (Rodgers), Craighead (Boyd), Hempstead (Singleton), Howard (McJunkins), Lonoke (Staley), Saline (Wright), Scott (Shores), White (Phillip Miller), Yell (Gault). Party is filled only where explicitly evidenced (Republican or Democratic); left blank for confirmed Independents (Columbia \u2014 Leroy Martin II) and where partisan affiliation was not independently verified, though most Arkansas sheriffs are Republican."
 }
